Last year, I fell in love with this boy who newly joined our college and what at first started to be a little crush expanded into something much more. He didn't care for me at all, in fact he treated me so badly i don't know at this point why i liked him so much but as time went on, the feeling of love i felt for him became to make me feel so painful. I became depressed, he started to become the only thing I cared about, I neglected everything for him even though he controlled every emotion of me and the only thing he did was make me sad and disappoint me. I really cared for him more than myself, I was failing school because I'd become so transfixed on becoming his ideal girl, I lost myself in the process, id become so different, i couldnt even recognise myself anymore and was becoming more and more distant from everyone else. I hated myself so much all the time, I always felt that I was never good enough for him and that he would never love me, all I saw were my weaknesses but i continously kept a strong image in front of him and lied through my teeth just so he would at least keep notice of me. I was so blind but I was convinced I was in love, I believed he was the only future I had, I didn't need anything or anyone else. Then one day, he started to treat me even more like trash and belittled my feelings and said some disgusting things then he blocked me. I'd never cried so much, my whole world that I'd built for myself was all for him, but it came crumbling down but as time went on I'd realised he had made me so ill both physically and mentally, whatever I felt for him, it can't have been love. I had fallen in love with the idea of him, it was all just an illusion, fake love. Now I can't even bear to crush on anyone ever again, I can't differentiate what true feelings are from fake feelings and just the thought of going through the that torture again makes me feel sick.

column3: In 2018-beginning of 2019, i wanted to kill myself, erase myself from this world. I felt like i was nothing. I felt like no one loved me. I felt that everyone hated me because of the mistakes i made. But in June 2019, i was on Youtube watching gacha life videos (it's a game if you didn't know) some of the youtubers who made gacha videos (we call them Gachatubers) and they were actually k-pop fans and i went to check them out and i listen to BTS first ( i actually knew them before from watching their performance on America's Got talent)I listen to Idol and i loved it. I listen to more kpop groups and fell in love. Although, i was still depressed. I got made fun at by my friends ( i still am but i don't care anymore, some of my friends still make fun of me not my best friend Berlin tho). some of my classmates ask me questions that i didn't want to answer but some of my classmates were really supported of me. My parents make fun of me as a joke and i still take it offending because i'm dumb and they are just playing around with me and my own mother calls me jungkook for crying out, i'm like MOM! I have no idea why she calls me it. So yeah, i was still depressed for a few months, Then i realize something, i was getting loved, not just my family and best friend but by ARMY too. Y'all really saved me. from depression. from suicide, from being someone i didnt want to be. My friends are huge anime fans ( i dont have a problem with that) and they been trying to pull me from the kpop community and trying to get me into the anime community. I only watch one anime which i really loved called of course Ouran High School Host Club its pretty obvious . im not really into anime anymore tho. i still respect the people who watch it tho but i'm starting to get pretty bore at it.

For anyone who didn't know the theory about Spring Day i will kindly explain to you here. I'm sure some of you have heard about the Sewol Ferry tragedy. Short info, the sinking of sewol ferry was an absolutely heart-breaking tragedy that resulted in a year long media blackout in order to cover the incident up. The ferry was a transport that went from Incheon to Jeju island, that at that time (April 2014) was carrying over 400 people. At some point it sank, resulting in the deaths over 300 people where most of the victims were high school students who were on a field trip at that time. Moving on, if you watch the first scene on Spring Day you can see Taehyung leaning his head on to the train track. There, he was feeling the survivor's guilt. The guilt of having survived while his friends have passed away. And then there was Jungkook looking outside the window. He is also a survivor, thinking about his lost friends. Next we have Jimin, he even goes back to the sea to reminisce. Next scene we have Namjoon rapping inside the train. Do you all notice the abandoned suitcases and clothes in that scene? Those abandoned stuff represent the students who went on the field trip with their belongings and never came back. It's widely known that the Korean Government has been heavily criticized by the way they handled the tragedy. In namjoon's lyrics he mentioned Snowpiercer Snowpiercer is a movie that symbolizes human society, where the people in front of the train (upper class & government) treats the tail of the train (regular people) in an inhumane way. And then Namjoon opened the door and we can see a big OMELAS sign. As Umu said, Omelas is a name of a fictional town in a book called The one who walk away from omelas The book explains about how someone's happiness means someone else's suffering. then we have Jin's scene. He represents the ones who have passed away. He looks up at all the other who are climbing and growing up while he is stuck at the bottom, unable to grow up. The rusty merry-go-around behind Jungkook represents a loss of childhood. And then skip to the part where Jimin symbolically picks up a pair of shoes of the survivor washed up on a shore. And then we have Yoongi sitting on a mountain pile of clothes. Those clothes represents all the victims. Skip to where Jungkook is standing still while the others are running behind him. As you can see there were yellow ribbons tied on the merry-go-around. Those ribbons are similar to the Sewol Ferry Yellow Ribbon Campaign and the next scene is where jungkook finally wakes up and run to seek justice for what happened. and then he thought he was fighting alone but then all the members showed up next to him. And then the train passed by, this scene symbolize that what's done is done. The dead won't come back to life. And then did you see the clothes outside the train? The clothes symbolizes how the dead is outside of the world (the world being the train) next there was a scene where all 7 of them sat on the mountain pile of clothes above the clouds (heaven) this scene symbolizes that all of the victims are in a better place. Last scene were they got off the train you can see a big tree. The tree represents hope, a new life, a spring day not a cold and dark winter day. And then Jimin hang a pair of shoes on the tree. In many cultures, shoes are hang on trees to commemorate the dead.
Fun fact: Suga and RM wrote this song at a park.

When I listened to the song the first time I cried. I entered a stage of depression and even started cutting.... once. I tried to be strong and remember that I have people who care... but it was hard. 1 month later I was considering listening to a BTS song, I had always dismissed it as weird and dumb. So I watched DNA and my world exploded. My friend that same day told me about BTS being extra af in America. I was hooked, I barely slept because I wanted to know everything, (that may sound bad but before this I was crying myself every night and I was very suicidal) I could tell them apart in less then a day. I met a incredible friend on discord who was a BTS stan and knew everything, till this day she is still patient enough to answer all of my questions. Then I realized something, my home life was improving, I wasn't procrastinating on my school work as much and for the first time in a long time I was caught up. I laughed at everything they did I cried at them being 100% real with ARMY and showing how much they truly cared. I felt loved. I felt happy. I felt alive. This group of 7 crackheaded boys, has single handily got rid of my depression improved my life at home and at school. Thank you thank you thank you thank you.  You have truly changed my life. This song is beautiful and pure and a god send. I listen to it whenever I feel down.
